node.title: AWS AI/ML Tech Talk Virtual Tour: Computer Vision Models
node.description:
RSVP on meetup is turned off, make sure to register here: https://learn.xnextcon.com/event/eventdetails/W20042918

This is online live event, you can join from anywhere around the world.
* Learn AI/ML through tech talks
* Q&A with experts
* Networking with peers
* Receive AWS credit provided by AWS team.

Computer Vision has received significant attention over the recent years, both within academia, and industry. As the state-of-the-art rapidly improves, the art-of-the-possible follows , offering innovative forms of computer vision applications for different scenarios. In this talk, Ramine will cover the background and development of computer vision, and demonstrate how to use AWS to build robust, computer vision models to perform object detection and classification.

Speaker:
Dr. Ramine Tinati, AWS Senior AI & Machine Learning Expert

KEY TAKEAWAYS
-Understand the history of Computer Vision
-Learn how to use Amazon SageMaker to build and Deploy Computer Vision Models
-How to orchestrate multiple models for implementing a real-world use case
- Receive AWS credit provided by AWS team

WHO SHOULD ATTEND
-Data Scientists
-Machine Learning Practitioners
-Developers interested in Machine Learning

RSVP: https://learn.xnextcon.com/event/eventdetails/W20042918

node.title: 4-week Online AI course: deep learning for developers
node.description:
We are starting again the new session for this popular 4-week AI course: Deep Learning for Developers.
Join hundreds of developers from all around the world to learn and practice AI and deep learning.

This course is online live course. You can listen, watch, interact, Q&A with instructors from anywhere around the world. If you miss the live session due to time zone or conflict, you can learn by watching session replay any time and live support on slack.

Start date: 28 April, 10am PT (US pacific time, check your local time zone).
* 8 sessions, 16 hours
* 10 live lectures, 16 hands-on code labs.
* Live Sessions, Real time interaction
* Forum supports to projects and homeworks

Details and Enrollment:
https://learn.xnextcon.com/course/coursedetails/C20042810
(after enroll, you will receive detail instructions to join the class)

Details:
learn deep learning by building deep learning models and projects.
The course takes unique project focused approach to teach you deep learning by building deep learning models. The instructor will walk you through a series of curated projects, and explain the key concepts as they arise. Students will learn the theory and how these models work under the hood while writing code, and building neural networks.

The course balances learning theory, working on projects, and also hearing from guest speakers who are industry practitioners in the field.

Students who take this course will be able to:
* Identify and frame problems that can be solved by deep learning
* Choose the right techniques to the problems
* Understand key deep learning concepts and how deep learning models work
* Identify and fix problems with messy datasets
* Build deep neural nets for classification and regression using the Keras framework
* Build convolutional neural networks for image classification, object localization and segmentation using the Keras
* Discuss the parts and processes involved in building large scale deep learning applications

Online AI tech talks, courses, bootcamps : https://learn.xnextcon.com

node.title: Online Workshop: The Power of Apache Cassandra, Apache Kafka and Elasticsearch
node.description:
This is online live tech workshop. You can join online using zoom (video conference tool), and watch, follow, Q&A with speakers from anywhere around the world. Miss the live session due to time zone or conflict? you can learn watch recording any time afterwards.

Registration:
https://zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_bRN9NiUDTuGuFfSG5rUQLw
(you must register at the website to receive the unique link to join the webinar).

Imagine being able to stream in data from multiple sources and create actionable search indexes and a permanent big data store. Now imagine using 100% license free open source technology! This is completely possible using Cassandra + Kafka + Elasticsearch and the connectors that link these systems.

In this workshop you will learn
- The merits of open source technology
- An introduction to Apache Cassandra, Apache Kafka and Elasticsearch
- The benefits of these open source technologies
- An example of an end to end integration workflow
- How to spin up clusters using our free trial
- Use case discussions currently impacting your enterprise

node.title: 4-weeks Online live AI course: full stack deep learning in AWS
node.description:
We are starting again the new session for this popular 4-week AI course: Full Stack Deep Learning with AWS.
The course has been scheduled for 3 times and sold out every class. Join hundreds of developers from all around the world to learn and practice AI and deep learning.

This course is online live course. You can listen, watch, interact, Q&A with instructors from anywhere around the world. If you miss the live session due to time zone or conflict, you can learn session replay any time afterwards.

Earn certificate upon course completion, Free trial, scholarship and job referral service is available.

Start date: Mar. 17, 5:30pm PT (US pacific time, check your local time zone).

* 4 weeks/ 8 sessions/ 12 hours
* 8 lectures / 8 hands-on projects/ 7 use cases
* Live Sessions, Real time interaction
* Forum supports to projects and homework

Enrollment:
https://learn.xnextcon.com/course/coursedetails/C2031717
(you must register at the website. after enroll, you will receive the link to join course online).

Details:
Many AI classes cover theoretical techniques of algorithms. In this workshop - we will train you to become a Full Stack Deep Learning Engineer, capable of not just training models but also deploying and managing them in production for business value. You will learn (and showcase) your Full Stack Deep Learning skills by building production Deep Learning microservices in AWS and a custom project that you can showcase to employers and peers.

This course has 8 hands on sessions where you will build, step by step, production grade Deep Learning services for business applications. You will learn how to build production AI in AWS, how to integrate it with an application, and how to manage an AI through its lifecycle. You will also build from scratch a custom project (where you will gather image data, train and tune a production grade neural network, build a prediction service, and connect that prediction service to create your own image processing AI application).

Details&Enrollment:
https://learn.xnextcon.com/course/coursedetails/C2031717

node.title: AWS AI Tech Talk Tour (Sydney): Building a Consumer Solution AI
node.description:
Building a Consumer Solution “Retail Assistant” AI with Amazon Sagemaker and AWS DeepLens

In this session I will show you how I build an iOT solution to solve my wife’s problem “What should I wear today?” We will start with how to build and deploy an Amazon Sagemaker object detection model on AWS DeepLens. Next, we will cover how to build a clothes identification system model using Amazon Sagemaker custom algorithm and executed it as a batch transform to save cost. Finally, we will cover how to glue the whole system together using AWS Lambda in a totally serverless architecture.

RSVP: https://awsaimlcommunitytour-syd.splashthat.com/

Agenda:
5:30PM: Welcome Drinks & Light Refreshments
Check-in to receive your AWS Credit + laptop sticker while you enjoy networking with your peers

6:00PM – 7:00PM: Session Start with AWS ML Hero, Agustinus Nalwan
Kick off the session with a technical deep dive from AI/ML expert

7:00PM – 7:30PM: Q&A
Stick around for a bit of 1:1 Q&A! Get your questions answered by our AWS Machine Learning Hero!

Speaker: Agustinus Nalwan, AWS Machine Learning Hero, Head of AI/ML Carsales.com.au
